  "name": "One Body, Two Minds",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/affliction_21.jpg",
  "sort": 0,
  "flags": {},
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 15th level, once per day, you can improve the effectiveness of a single spell by having your possessing spirit channel that spell. The spell acts as though it were affected by both the @Compendium[pf1.feats.2YuxcUNFMPNBpekG]{Silent Spell} and @Compendium[pf1.feats.jVFjMIyQD6TOAsmj]{Still Spell} <em>metamagic feats</em>. If the spell chosen is a <em>mind-affecting</em> spell, it also benefits from the @Compendium[pf1.feats.btXWioB3SKJv8YEG]{Extend Spell} <em>metamagic feat</em>. This ability does not use up a spell slot higher than the level of the base spell, nor does it increase the level of the base spell.</p>"
    },
